title: Human Anatomy
description: Detailed study of human body structures using a regional and systems approach.  Emphasis is placed on structural relationships and the integration of body systems.
restrictions: __HEADER_0__Must be enrolled in one of the following Campuses:
prerequisites: ((BIOS 1108 Undergraduate Semester Minimum Grade of D and BIOS 1108L Undergraduate Semester Minimum Grade of D or (BIOS 1208 Undergraduate Semester Minimum Grade of D and BIOS 1208L Undergraduate Semester Minimum Grade of D) or BIOL 1520 Undergraduate Semester Minimum Grade of D or BIOL 1521 Undergraduate Semester Minimum Grade of D) or (CHEM 1211K Undergraduate Semester Minimum Grade of D or CHEM 1310 Undergraduate Semester Minimum Grade of D))
